'''Puddle''', ''v., intr.'' [Middle English ''podel'', diminutive of Old English ''pudd'', ditch.](1) The act or pastime of redistributing liquid, oft. violently, from existing puddles, esp. of rain water, by stomping and any kind of jumping and rollicking about.  (2) Any activity that purposes or requires one to traverse puddles.  (3)  The collection of liquid into puddles. (4) The collection of ideas, esp. absract concepts, into rough subtopics or categories, as in study, research or conversation. ''Puddled'', ''puddling'', ''puddler''.

